Q1: Verify your current working directory ?

pwd

notes: PWD is Present working directory command in linux 

Q2: List "/etc" directory files and directories ?

ls /etc 

notes:List command for listing is ls and mentioning the directory will help us list files in the directory 

Q3: List ".conf" files only under "/etc" directory ?

ls /etc/*.conf

notes using list command and an * as an wild card character to caputure all the .conf files in the directory (we can also use -l for getting more details such as Filetype, permission)

Q4: Print total number of ".conf" files only under "/etc" directory ?

ls /etc/*.conf | wc -l

notes: Pipeline is usually used as an step 2 of the command once step 1 is executed and wc -l counts the lines which has *.conf in the direcotry

Q5: Create an empty directory with name "bash" under "/tmp" directory ?

mkdir /tmp/bash 

Notes: mkdir is make directory an command used to make directory in linux systems

Q6: Create an empty file with name "devops.txt" under "/tmp/bash/" directory ?

touch /tmp/bash/devops.txt

Notes: Touch command is used to create an file in linux file systems


